terministic dependencies are added. Notably, Java 21 lacks JAXB, which is useful to know. The user specifically wants research, not modifications, so I'll provide concise reasons. Generated tests might need to create and stop an in-process HTTP endpoint, and I’ll ensure no additional system properties or environment settings are required for this setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test setup**\\n\\nI need to clarify that tests shouldn't set any system properties. The in-process server doesn't count as an environment or system property, but \\\"other test-code setup\\\" does apply here. I'll use \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" to note that there's no need for deterministic dependencies. It seems the resolved artifact only relies on jersey-core, and the default handler uses JDK HttpURLConnection. The documentation mentions HTTP WebResource, so no Docker is needed. I'll remember to keep everything in plain JSON without any markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jersey Client 1.9 is an HTTP REST client; meaningful coverage needs an actual HTTP endpoint, but the resolved artifact only requires jersey-core and the default connector uses JDK HttpURLConnection, so no extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Create and stop an in-process local HTTP endpoint in the generated tests, preferably JDK com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpServer bound to 127.0.0.1 on a random port, then exercise Client.create(), WebResource, GET/POST, headers, ClientResponse, and filters against that endpoint. No environment variables or system properties are required. Prefer text/plain, application/x-www-form-urlencoded, headers, and status-code coverage with the default URLConnection connector.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Documentation examples often show JSON/JAXB entity mapping; those paths may require optional Jersey JSON/JAXB dependencies that are not transitively supplied by com.sun.jersey:jersey-client:1.9, especially on JDK 21.\",\n    \"Avoid Apache HTTP client connector coverage unless an explicit optional connector dependency is added; the default Client.create() path uses HttpURLConnection and needs no extra dependency.\",\n    \"Do not rely on public external HTTP services; use a local in-process server for deterministic Gradle and Native Image verification.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02b46d10f058401d016a41378ba0088196ad8fca39b0279423\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 252, "output": 1330, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27182, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782658937070, "responseId": "resp_02b46d10f058401d016a41377983608196a5800ed609160b06"}, "toolResults": []}
